analysis: The documents primarily concern the establishment, modification, and oversight of governmental boards, councils, committees, and interagency groups. They detail the composition, functions, and responsibilities of these entities, often focusing on coordination, policy development, and interagency cooperation. The documents also cover specific areas such as water resources, economic policy, Indian affairs, regional operations, minority business development, radio frequencies, and research councils.
title: Governmental Boards and Interagency Groups
